0she%20recognized%20him%20immediately.%20She%20was%20thrilled%2C%20giving%20little%20jumps%20into%20the%20air%20with%20a%20huge%20smile%2C%20and%20threw%20her%20arms%20around%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20then%20she%20saw%20my%20oldest%20son.%20He%20was%20only%206%20the%20last%20time%20he%20visited%2C%20yet%20somehow%2C%20she%20still%20knew%20his%20trademark%20curls.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BBaby%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20signed.%20I%20remembered%20the%20time%20she%20fed%20him%20a%20bottle%20when%20he%20was%206%20months%20old%2C%20marveling%20at%20how%20intuitively%20she%20knew%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20leaned%20close%20to%20him%2C%20now%20nearly%20as%20tall%20as%20she%20was.%20An%20inch%20from%20his%20face%2C%20she%20studied%20it%20all%20%E2%80%94%20his%20green%20eyes%2C%20braces%2C%20that%20long%20hair.%20He%20laughed%20nervously.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20sure%20what%20to%20do%2C%20Mom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20assured%20him.%20%26quot%3BRemember%2C%20she%20can%20barely%20see%2C%20so%20she%20needs%20to%20get%20close.%20But%20she%20remembers%20you%2C%20honey.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20they%20hugged%2C%20my%20sister's%20peals%20of%20laughter%20filling%20the%20room.%20My%204-year-old%2C%20never%20one%20to%20sit%20out%20of%20the%20spotlight%2C%20began%20pulling%20her%20arm%20and%20demanding%20her%20attention.%20She%20looked%20down%2C%20giggled%2C%20and%20patted%20his%20head.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22226faf51-4295-410d-b441-67fead322a83%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKids%20don't%20hold%20biases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20tears%20spilled%20over%20before%20I%20even%20felt%20them%20coming%20on%2C%20and%20I%20stepped%20away%20silently%20into%20the%20bathroom.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'd%20been%20so%20scared%20the%20trip%2