o%20do%20all%20three%20of%20those%20things%2C%20and%20her%20two%20children%2C%20JR%20and%20Jocelyn%2C%20had%20front-row%20seats.%20Here%20are%20three%20important%20lessons%20that%20Adams%20said%20her%20children%20learned%20simply%20by%20watching%20her%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ecf0fdf-778e-468c-a6ef-470c1b8b16ec%5C%22%3E1.%20Asking%20questions%20about%20money%20and%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20plays%20an%20NPR%20podcast%20called%20Marketplace%20Money%20in%20front%20of%20her%20kids.%20%26quot%3BThey%20hate%20talk%20radio%2C%20but%20I%20can%20tell%20it%20makes%20a%20difference.%20They%20learn%20a%20thing%20or%20two%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20kids%20weren't%20afraid%20to%20ask%20questions%20about%20why%20businesses%20closed%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20Adams%20did%20her%20best%20to%20answer.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20talking%20about%20why%20some%20stores%20went%20out%20of%20business%2C%20and%20I%20had%20the%20chance%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20the%20supply%20chain%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20says%20her%20kids%20were%20upset%20when%20Chick-fil-A%20ran%20out%20of%20sauces%2C%20and%20she%20used%20that%20opportunity%20to%20explain%20that%20there's%20a%20high%20demand%20for%20goods%20and%20a%20low%20supply%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BThat%20Chick-fil-A%20sauce%2C%20that%20was%20ruining%20their%20life%20for%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270336ba7-ee34-4c53-91af-ce333642374c%5C%22%3E2.%20The%20importance%20of%20a%20strong%20work%20ethic%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20kids%20understand%20that%20if%20I%20don't%20kill%20it%2C%20I%20don't%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20kids%20ask%20why%20I'm%20still%20on%20my%20computer%20answering%20emails%20later%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20and%20I%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20there's%20people%20in%20California%20that%20are%20still%20working.%20People%20in%20Hawaii%20are%20just%20getting%20their%20day%20started.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20kids%20understand%20that%20the%20hours%20their%20mom%20puts%20into%20her%20work%20directly%20translates%20into%20food%20on%20the%20table%20and%20a%20roof%20over%20their%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a3b3f8e7-8821-49b3-a974-5907303a8d3e%5C%22%3E3.%20How%20to%20work%20toward%20long-term%20goals%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20that%20her%20work%20as%20a%20debt%20payoff%20coach%20gives%20her%20children%20a%20unique%20perspective%20on%20delayed%20gratification%2C%20helping%20them%20work%20toward%20their%20long-term%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20in%20on%20the%20deeper%20conversations%20that%20parents%20need%20to%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20you%20can%20start%20with%20explaining%20why%20they%20can't%20get%20a%20toy%20at%20Walmart%20or%20Target.%26quot%3B%20When%20her%20kids%20ask%20for%20toys%2C%20she%20reminds%20them%20of%20their%20long-term%20goal%20of%20going%20to%20Disneyland%20for%20their%20birthday%20or%20a%20bigger%20present%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20mindset%20helps%20them%20understand%20delayed%20gratification%2C%20and%20Adams%20hopes%20it%20fosters%20a%20healthy%20relationship%20with%20debt%20and%20money%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20know%20where%20to%20start%3F%20Consider%20a%20financial%20advisor.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20who%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20