ber%2C%20among%20the%20lowest%20since%20mid-2020%20%E2%80%94%20and%20an%20over%2080%25%20reduction%20since%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Trump's%20first%20term%20in%20office%2C%20the%20US%20deported%20about%201.5%20million%20people.%20Between%20January%202021%20and%20August%202024%2C%20when%20Biden%20held%20office%2C%20more%20than%201.4%20million%20deportations%20were%20carried%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2278450d2a-2ca7-45b1-9e05-ef5e2dcbbc15%5C%22%3EMass%20deportations%20could%20hurt%20American%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Trump's%20arguments%20about%20immigrants%20is%20that%20they%20steal%20jobs%20from%20native-born%20workers.%20Recent%20research%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32389%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS-born%20employment%3C%2Fa%3E%20increases%20with%20immigration%2C%20and%20deportations%20hurt%20native%20job%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUS-born%20workers%20do%20not%20simply%20take%20all%20the%20jobs%20left%20behind%20by%20immigrants%20after%20they%20are%20deported%2C%26quot%3B%20Chloe%20East%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20who%20studies%20immigration%20policy%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20because%20these%20jobs%20are%20lower-paid%2C%20more%20dangerous%2C%20and%20otherwise%20less%20desirable%20than%20the%20jobs%20more%20often%20taken%20by%20US-born%20workers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20already%20seen%20examples%20of%20this%20in%20its%20recent%20history.%20Around%20400%2C000%20people%20were%20deported%20between%202008%20and%202014%20through%20a%20program%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fthe-labor-market-impact-of-deportations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESecure%20Communities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Research%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epublished%20in%20October%20showed%20industries%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.trouphoward.com%2Fuploads%2F1%2F2%2F7%2F7%2F127764736%2Fhoward_wang_zhang_cracking_down_pricing_up_ssrn_nov_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheightened%20worker%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20included%20the%20construction%20workforce%2C%20which%20employs%20among%20the%20highest%20numbers%20of%20workers%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20labor%20market%20is%20already%20tense%20and%20tight%2C%20and%20construction%20is%20one%20of%20those%20industries%20that%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennie%20Murray%2C%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20immigrant%20advocacy%20nonprofit%20group%20National%20Immigration%20Forum%2C%20told%20BI.%20She%20added%20that%20deportations%20could%20worsen%20housing%20shortages%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20may%20feel%20the%20effects%20of%20deportations%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20as%20a%20reduced%20agricultural%20workforce%20could%20mean%20less%20locally%20sourced%20food%20and%20higher%20prices.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.americanprogress.org%2Fcontent%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F01%2F01114806%2FEW-FoodSupply-factsheet.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20American%20Progress%3C%2Fa%3E%20analysis%20from%202021%20found%20that%20nearly%20300%2C000%20workers%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20were%20in%20agriculture%20and%20farming%20%E2%80%94%20around%2013%25%20of%20the%202.3%20million%20workers%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNS12034560%230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagriculture%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b58fe86e-e2ff-41d7-b640-22fe29d1b96e%5C%22%3EThe%20broader%20economy%20could%20be%20impacted%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EImmigrants%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20also%20contribute%20significantly%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-pay-in-taxes-trump-tax-bill-expiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20government%20programs.%20In%202022%2C%20they%20paid%20%2496.7%20billion%20in%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%20local%20taxes%2C%20per%20the%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitep.org%2Fundocumented-immigrants-taxes-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20from%20the%20Institute%20on%20Taxation%20and%20Economic%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20paid%20%2425.7%20billion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-regrets-401k-divorce-moving-financial-mistakes-aarp-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20taxes%20and%20%246.4%20billion%20in%20Medicare%20taxes%20while%20being%20ineligible%20to%20receive%20benefits%20from%20those%20social%20insurance%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Republicans%20have%20argued%20that%20welfare%20programs%20and%20taxpayer-subsidized%20health%20insurance%20for%20immigrants%20have%20cost%20US%20residents%20billions%2C%20potentially%20partly%20offsetting%20these%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20think%20tanks%20said%20the%20broader%20economy%20could%20suffer%20if%20millions%20of%20people%20are%20deported.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fblogs%2Frealtime-economics%2F2024%2Fmass-deportations-would-harm-us-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeterson%20Institute%20for%20International%20Economics%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote%20in%20September%20that%20if%201.3%20million%20people%20are%20deported%2C%20GDP%20could%20fall%201.2%25%20below%20baseline%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-first-day-immigration-executive-orders-deportations-border-visas-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737397878000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678eb2fc2fcded5e9073e8f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%