not%20put%20enough%20pressure%20on%20Israel.%20In%20May%202023%2C%20Biden%20had%20put%20a%20ceasefire%20deal%20on%20the%20negotiating%20table%2C%20but%20Israel's%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20used%20delaying%20tactics%20in%20alliance%20with%20his%20ultra-nationalist%20coalition%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Mini-cabinet'%20in%20UK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%20per%20BBC%20sources%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20series%20of%20secret%20%26quot%3Bmini-cabinet%26quot%3B%20meetings%20with%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Sir%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20the%20Chancellor%20Rachel%20Reeves%2C%20the%20Foreign%20Secretary%20David%20Lammy%2C%20and%20the%20Business%20Secretary%20Jonathan%20Reynolds%2C%20in%20anticipation%20of%20what's%20to%20come%20or%20%26quot%3Btrying%20to%20plan%20for%20what%20might%20come%26quot%3B.%20Although%20there%20hasn't%20been%20too%20much%20preparation%20as%20the%20source%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou'd%20drive%20yourself%20crazy%26quot%3B%20trying%20to%20understand%20Trump's%20fickle%20steps.%20However%20another%20source%20informed%20that%20various%20papers%20have%20been%20prepared%20to%20be%20presented%20to%20the%20entire%20Cabinet.%20The%20uncertainty%20that%20Trump%20brings%20along%20with%20him%20is%20what%20the%20British%20political%20establishment%20finds%20shocking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia-Ukraine%20war%20settlement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Russians%20keep%20moving%20forward%2C%20the%20Trump%20presidency%20will%20bring%20with%20itself%20pressure%20-%20for%20a%20deal%2C%20and%20that%20most%20probably%20will%20not%20be%20on%20Ukraine's%20terms.%20On%20the%20campaign%20trail%20itself%2C%20Trump%20had%20vowed%20to%20end%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20saying%20he%20would%20do%20it%20in%20%26quot%3B24%20hours%26quot%3B%20after%20taking%20oath.%20However%2C%20General%20Keith%20Kellogg%2C%20his%20envoy%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%20now%20says%20that%20it%20can%20be%20hoped%20that%20the%20deal%20will%20be%20reached%20within%20the%20first%20100%20days%20of%20Trump's%20presidency.%20Moreover%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20in%20televised%20remarks%2C%20while%20congratulating%20Trump%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20also%20open%20to%20dialogue%20with%20the%20new%20US%20administration%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20conflict%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20also%20added%20that%20the%20deal%20should%20ensure%2C%20%26quot%3Blasting%20peace%20based%20on%20respect%20for%20the%20legitimate%20interests%20of%20all%20people%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20tariff%20threat%20to%20Canada%20amid%20turmoil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada%20is%20going%20through%20a%20period%20of%20political%20instability%2C%20fuelled%20by%20Trump's%20threat%20of%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20Canadian%20goods%20by%20the%20US.%20Until%20recently%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20was%20determined%20to%20stay%20in%20office%2C%20eager%20to%20face%20off%20against%20his%20ideological%20opposite%2C%20Pierre%20Poilievre%2C%20in%20the%20polls.%20However%2C%20the%20sudden%20resignation%20of%20his%20key%20deputy%2C%20Chrystia%20Freeland%2C%20in%20mid-December%2C%20citing%20Trudeau's%20perceived%20failure%20to%20take%20Trump's%20threats%20seriously%2C%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFreeland's%20resignation%20sparked%20a%20wave%20of%20dissent%20within%20Trudeau's%20own%20party%2C%20with%20many%20members%20publicly%20withdrawing%20their%20support%20for%20his%20leadership.%20This%20internal%20backlash%20ultimately%20led%20to%20Trudeau's%20resignation%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20in%20leadership%20comes%20at%20a%20critical%20time%20for%20Canada%2C%20which%20is%20navigating%20a%20complex%20web%20of%20challenges%2C%20including%20the%20potential%20tariffs%20and%20ongoing%20diplomatic%20tensions%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPotential%20US-China%2